{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017euyfYKxivVRa4uDZ7mT8A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"As expected, `systeminformation` is not in the project's package.json (it's review material only). I'll note this in the consultation.\n\nNow let me package the consultation. I have 6 solid OWASP-tagged findings from `disk-info.ts`. Let me also include the admin-bypass finding from `handler.ts` since it's a sibling file in scope.\n\nLet me curate the top 5 findings for the consultation:\n1. Command injection vulnerability at line 35 (critical severity)\n2. Hardcoded secret at line 20 (critical severity)\n3. Path traversal vulnerability at line 46 (critical severity)\n4. Sensitive data transmitted over plain HTTP at lines 68-69 (important severity)\n5. Vulnerable dependency issue noted in comments (important severity)\n6. Security logging failure at lines 55-60 (important severity)\n\nThere's also an admin bypass vulnerability in handler.ts at line 21 where an attacker can manipulate a JSON field to bypass access controls, plus an audit logging gap at lines 57-61. The core threat model centers on disk-info.ts accepting user-supplied mount paths that get passed directly into shell commands, creating a command injection vector that could compromise the entire server, expose API credentials, and grant unauthorized filesystem access.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1342,"cache_read_input_tokens":66143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1342},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"982c880a-149c-4384-b368-23569ac111e3","uuid":"bdfb4c19-3dfa-437b-920f-281d0f6088b5","request_id":"req_011CbrVA3NZn2u4bYWJCK49U"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017euyfYKxivVRa4uDZ7mT8A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scan complete. I have 6 OWASP-tagged findings across both files. Packaging the consultation for the security-reviewer agent now."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1342,"cache_read_input_tokens":66143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1342},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"982c880a-149c-4384-b368-23569ac111e3","uuid":"7d38697d-5e84-4b41-84c4-c8d112984230","request_id":"req_011CbrVA3NZn2u4bYWJCK49U"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017euyfYKxivVRa4uDZ7mT8A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019LRJspYMz5AqHE8vPzyzev","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Security review of disk-info.ts","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:security-reviewer","prompt":"## Review Scope\n\nSecurity review of `review-src/disk-info.ts` -- a disk-usage query module that shells out to `du`, queries filesystem size via a third-party library, and caches results to an internal HTTP endpoint. The sibling file `review-src/handler.ts` is included in scope as it shares the same directory and contains attack-chain-relevant patterns.\n\n## Threat Model Context\n\n**Protected assets:**\n- Server filesystem (arbitrary read/write/execute via shell)\n- Hardcoded API token (`sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1`) embedded in source\n- Internal cache endpoint at `http://cache.internal/store`\n- Network traffic carrying the token (plaintext HTTP)\n\n**Actor profile:**\n- Any consumer that can supply a `DiskQuery` object with `mountPath` -- likely a web API or IPC caller; no input trust assumed\n- Attacker controlling `query.mountPath` gains direct leverage over shell execution and filesystem traversal\n\n**Blast radius:**\n- Full server compromise via command injection (shell escape in `exec`)\n- Credential theft from source code or network interception\n- Unauthorized filesystem traversal beyond intended mount points\n- Silent failure suppression hiding active exploitation\n\n## Findings\n\n1. **Command Injection**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:35`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP category: A03 Injection\n   - Description: `query.mountPath` flows from caller input through no validation into a string-concatenated shell command passed to `exec`. Input like `\"/mnt; rm -rf /\"` executes arbitrary shell commands with the process's privileges.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const path = query.mountPath;\n     exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n     ```\n\n2. **Hardcoded Secret / Live API Token**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP category: A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n   - Description: A live API token (`sk_live_...`) is hardcoded in source. Any repository reader obtains it; it cannot be rotated without a code change; and it appears in VCS history permanently even after removal.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n     ```\n\n3. **Path Traversal**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP category: A01 Broken Access Control\n   - Description: The same unvalidated `path` (attacker-controlled `mountPath`) is passed directly to `fsSize()`. Input like `\"../../etc\"` or `\"../../root/.ssh\"` allows traversal outside the intended mount scope, exposing sensitive filesystem entries.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const size = await fsSize(path);\n     return { path, size };\n     ```\n\n4. **Sensitive Data Over Plain HTTP / Token in Query Parameter**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:68-69`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP category: A02 Cryptographic Failures\n   - Description: The API token is transmitted over plain `http://` (not `https://`) and placed in the URL query string. This exposes the credential in network traffic, server access logs, proxy logs, and browser history. A second command injection exists here: user-controlled `parsed` data is interpolated into a shell command via `exec('curl ...')`.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n     void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n     ```\n\n5. **Security Logging / Monitoring Failure -- Silent Error Suppression**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:55-60`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP category: A09 Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\n   - Description: The `cacheResult` function swallows all errors with an empty catch block. This suppresses security-relevant failures (parse errors from injected output, cache write failures, downstream errors) and eliminates any audit trail that would detect active exploitation.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     try {\n       const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n       writeCache(parsed);\n     } catch (_) {\n       // swallowed\n     }\n     ```\n\n6. **Vulnerable Dependency Pin**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:9-13` (comment block)\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP category: A06 Vulnerable and Outdated Components\n   - Description: The module pins `systeminformation@3.42.0` -- a version that predates command-injection advisories patched in later major releases. The package is declared as review material only and not installed in the project's `package.json`, so `npm audit` cannot confirm the specific CVEs; however, the stated version is far behind the current major and the comment explicitly names command-injection advisories as the concern.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     // \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT (vulnerable dep pin)\n     import { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n     ```\n\n7. **Admin Privilege Escalation via Unvalidated Attacker-Controlled Field (sibling file)**\n   - File: `review-src/handler.ts:17,21`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP category: A01 Broken Access Control\n   - Description: `handleRequest` parses untrusted `req.body` via `JSON.parse` with no try/catch (crash on malformed input) and then gates admin processing on `payload.admin === true` -- a field fully controlled by the attacker. Any caller can escalate to admin by supplying `{\"admin\":true,...}` in the request body. No server-side authorization check exists.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const payload = JSON.parse(req.body);\n     if (payload.admin === true) return processAdmin(payload);\n     ```\n\n## Request\n\nValidate these 7 findings against OWASP Top 10. Confirm or revise my initial severity assignments. Flag any attack chains across findings (e.g., command injection + silent error suppression enabling persistent access without detection). Identify any cross-cutting patterns or additional threat vectors I may have missed."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1342,"cache_read_input_tokens":66143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1342},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"982c880a-149c-4384-b368-23569ac111e3","uuid":"e2ddbe34-0678-4a10-b3be-19a0c98e910c","request_id":"req_011CbrVA3NZn2u4bYWJCK49U"}
